279
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:47,130
Now, for tax hacking,

280
00:11:47,130 --> 00:11:49,200
I know this one might sound a bit dodgy,

281
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:50,850
but trust me, there are lots

282
00:11:50,850 --> 00:11:53,730
of ways you can legally
keep more of your money.

283
00:11:53,730 --> 00:11:57,210
One great tax hack is to
take advantage of deductions.

284
00:11:57,210 --> 00:11:58,470
If you have a small business

285
00:11:58,470 --> 00:12:01,020
or side hustle, you can reduce your taxes

286
00:12:01,020 --> 00:12:04,350
by claiming expenses like
a home office, internet

287
00:12:04,350 --> 00:12:06,930
or travel as long as
they're used for business.

288
00:12:06,930 --> 00:12:09,930
Another is using tax-free
savings accounts.

289
00:12:09,930 --> 00:12:11,200
In the UK, you can save up

290
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:15,450
to 20,000 pounds per year in
an ISA where all your interest

291
00:12:15,450 --> 00:12:17,010
and gains are tax free.

292
00:12:17,010 --> 00:12:20,460
In the USA, you have a similar
option like the Roth IRA.

293
00:12:20,460 --> 00:12:23,700
Tax Hacking is all about
understanding the rules wherever

294
00:12:23,700 --> 00:12:26,670
you are and using them to
keep more of what you earn.

295
00:12:26,670 --> 00:12:29,910
The aim is to pay what you
owe, but not a penny more.

296
00:12:29,910 --> 00:12:32,430
Now, let's talk about deal hacking.

297
00:12:32,430 --> 00:12:34,830
This is all about negotiation.

298
00:12:34,830 --> 00:12:36,750
Let's say you are looking to buy a car,

299
00:12:36,750 --> 00:12:38,760
never accept the sticker price.

300
00:12:38,760 --> 00:12:40,470
That's what the dealership wants.

301
00:12:40,470 --> 00:12:43,320
Remember, the first
price is rarely the best.

302
00:12:43,320 --> 00:12:47,010
Do your research first so you
know the car's market value.

303
00:12:47,010 --> 00:12:48,660
Get quotes from a few dealers

304
00:12:48,660 --> 00:12:51,270
so you can say the dealer
down the road has offered me

305
00:12:51,270 --> 00:12:54,330
a much better deal and actually
be able to back this up

306
00:12:54,330 --> 00:12:56,580
as it puts you in a
much stronger position.

307
00:12:56,580 --> 00:12:59,550
The easiest way to find out
the true value of a car is

308
00:12:59,550 --> 00:13:02,100
to pretend you are selling
the one you are looking at

309
00:13:02,100 --> 00:13:05,610
to a car buying service
like CarMax or Carvana.

310
00:13:05,610 --> 00:13:08,370
Check out what they'd
offer you for it online.

311
00:13:08,370 --> 00:13:10,980
You want to pay as close
to this price as possible

312
00:13:10,980 --> 00:13:13,320
to ensure you're not
overpaying for the car.

313
00:13:13,320 --> 00:13:16,080
Also, buying at the
right time matters too.

314
00:13:16,080 --> 00:13:18,180
If you go at the end of
the month when salespeople

315
00:13:18,180 --> 00:13:20,100
are trying to hit sales targets,

316
00:13:20,100 --> 00:13:21,720
you'll often find a better deal.

317
00:13:21,720 --> 00:13:24,000
These strategies have saved me thousands

318
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:25,260
on cars over the years

319
00:13:25,260 --> 00:13:27,090
and they work for lots
of other things too,

320
00:13:27,090 --> 00:13:30,180
so don't be afraid to
ask for a better price.

321
00:13:30,180 --> 00:13:33,090
Everything's negotiable if
you know how to play the game.

322
00:13:33,090 --> 00:13:35,160
Step three is to get a credit card.

323
00:13:35,160 --> 00:13:37,110
The biggest lie young people are told is

324
00:13:37,110 --> 00:13:40,108
that credit cards are evil and
that you shouldn't have one.

325
00:13:40,108 --> 00:13:43,110
A lot of people think credit
cards are just a quick way

326
00:13:43,110 --> 00:13:45,930
